name: Bed Bath & Beyond
directions: The bathrooms are towards the right side of the store once you enter.  Go past the cashier stations and go into the towels section, and you'll see them on the right.  They are gender specific, single person bathrooms.  I think they are wheelchair accessible, but I am not sure.  There are wheelchair parking spots outside, so I would assume so.
comment: Store hours:  Mon-Sat: 9:00am - 9:00pm, Sun: 10:00am - 7:00pm

name: PetSmart Hyannis, Massachusetts
directions: The bathrooms are on the right side of the store, half way back and behind the adoption room.  There are gender-specific single person bathrooms.  I can't remember if they are wheelchair accessible, but I think so.  There are ramps outside and wheelchair parking spots, so I would assume so.
comment: Store hours are 9-9 Monday through Saturday, and 10-6 Sundays.

name: Student Health Centre, University of Windsor
directions: Second floor of CAW
comment: There are 2 unisex bathrooms inside the student health centre. They are in the doctor's area and not the waiting area, but they are there if you don't mind asking the receptionists.

name: Burgerfuel-The Base Te Awa
street: Shop 55R, Te Awa Shopping Centre (Corner Te Rapa Road and Wairere Drive)
comment: It's a restaurant. Gender neutral single stall toilet.

name: Gothenburg Restaurant
directions: Inside the ANZ building on Grantham Street.
comment: It's a restaurant. Unisex single occupancy toilets.

name: Wendy's
directions: In the back.
comment: Enter by the side door and the only people who will see you are other customers.

name: 273-275 Main St, Northampton, MA 01060, USA
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Elk Brewing
comment: All bathrooms are unisex, single occupant

name: Augie's Coffee

name: Boon Burger
directions: On the 1st Floor. Enter 141 Bannatyne Ave, and walk right past the Boon Burger entrance. Keep walking all the way past the elevator through the door that says "exit". Once you walk through the "exit" door, the bathrooms are the 2nd door – clearly marked, and accessible.
comment:
Building hours for public washroom are:
Mon-Sat: 11am - 10pm
Sun: 11am - 4pm

name: Humanitree House

name: Colorado Welcome center rest area

name: Maple City Market

comment: Small, single user bathroom.

name: Identity Salon Spa & Tanning

name: Portland State University 5th Avenue Cinema

name: Topper's Pizza

name: Hamilton Hall
directions: From the east entrance, take the stairs down to the basement and walk down the hall and there will be a smaller hallway with two unisex bathrooms on your right. Or take the east elevator down, 180-degree left into that hallway, same deal.
comment: It's on campus but pretty unlikely that you MUST be student/faculty/staff to use. There's hardly anyone walking around the basement, just people in their offices.

name: Solera/Cheshire
directions: One small restroom downstairs and one large restroom upstairs

name: It's a Grind

name: Pearl Cup @ AT&T Performing Arts Center

comment: Closed Mondays

name: Newman Library
directions: 3rd floor by the stairway

name: barrio

name: Zavino University City

name: Chill Bar

name: Dust Covenant Church
directions: Second floor of the State Farm building, near the back (labeled with gender-neutral signage)
comment: Make sure to check hours (http://www.dustchurch.com/house-of-study/hours). The space is LGBTQ+-friendly.

name: Virginia Tech - Pritchard Hall
directions: Located on the 3rd floor (near 3030s and 3040s), the closest entrance is located off of Washington Street SW

name: Spokane Valley High School
directions: The two portables on the left side both have gender neutral bathrooms, and there is a "staff" bathroom in the corridor leading to the Big Room that is gender neutral.
comment: Students and staff only. Using the "staff" bathroom might get you in trouble depending on which teacher sees you, but most will be accepting if you explain why you need a gender neutral bathroom.

name: Northland College
directions:
There is an "All Gender" restroom with multiple stalls, hygiene receptacles, and a needle disposal on the first floor of the Ponzio Student Center near the cafeteria. 
There are two single stalled "All Gender" restrooms on the first floor of the Dexter Library in the back right corner of the building.
comment: Anyone can use them!

name: Flightpath Coffee House
comment: They've relatively recently changed both of their restroom signs to be unisex. The front entrance has an awkward narrow slope that is not exactly the most accessible.
